# Local dev-only tooling for api/ and training/ (uv-managed pytest/ruff/mypy).
# Vercel's Python runtime deps come from api/requirements.txt (each Python
# service in vercel.json is rooted at api/ and installs from there). Keeping
# api/pyproject.toml + api/uv.lock out of the upload matters: a service
# rooted at api/ would otherwise read them as the dependency manifest and
# deploy the dev-only toolchain instead of the runtime deps.
api/pyproject.toml
api/uv.lock
api/tests
api/.venv
api/.pytest_cache
api/__pycache__

training/

# Never upload env files (.vercelignore replaces .gitignore for uploads)
# or local dependency trees.
.env*
**/node_modules

# Not consumed by the Vercel build: poller/ deploys via wrangler; data/,
# db/, docs/, scripts/, .github/ are repo-side only. Python functions
# bundle "all reachable files" (no tree-shaking), so keeping these out of
# the upload also keeps them out of the function bundles (225 MB cap).
poller/
data/
db/
docs/
scripts/
.github/
.gstack/
*.md
